# Tool Intro Splash вАФ Non-Distort Maximized Layout

All cinematic fullscreen tool intros (`*IntroGate.tsx` + `*-landing.css`) inherit layout from `src/components/tool-intro-splash.css` (via `globals.css`).

## Required shell

```tsx
<div className="{prefix}-fs tool-intro-fs">
  <header className="{prefix}-fs__header">вА¶</header>
  <div className="{prefix}-fs__stage">
    <div className="{prefix}-fs__scene">
      <div className="{prefix}-fs__workspace animation-workspace">
        <div className="{prefix}-fs__card">{/* animation */}</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div className="{prefix}-fs__footer">
    <button className="{prefix}-fs__cta">Get Started</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

- Always include `tool-intro-fs` on the root and `animation-workspace` on the workspace.
- Optional aliases: `global-splash-workspace`, `global-splash-card`.
- Keep success badges **inside** `__card` so they are not clipped.

## Global footprint (caps + center вАФ never full-stage stretch)

| Zone | Standard |
|------|----------|
| Stage | Flex-centered, `max-height: calc(100vh - 180px)` |
| Workspace | `flex: 0 1 auto` (must not grow across the scene), `max-width: min(var(--splash-max-width, 560px), 90%)`, `margin: 0 auto` |
| Inner `__card` / cardless visual | Same width ceiling, `max-height: min(60vh, 28rem)`, `object-fit: contain`, `margin: 0 auto` |

**Do not** force cards to a fixed wide banner (e.g. `width: 100%` of the stage, `780px`, or `max-width: 100%` alone). Horizontal designs stretch that way.

Tool CSS owns native proportions (`clamp()`, aspect-ratio, fixed preview sizes). Shared CSS only centers, caps, and uniformly zooms.

### Horizontal / wide cards

For landscape shells (Rotate PDF, Video Rotator, conversion stage-art, etc.):

- Prefer `width: 90%`, `max-width: 520pxвАУ560px`, `margin-inline: auto`
- Balanced height: `height/max-height: min(48vh, 380px)`, `min-height: ~280вАУ300px` вАФ not a flat strip, not overlapping text
- Keep a modest gap under the subtitle (`padding-top` / `margin-top` ~8вАУ20px); header stays `z-index: 3`
- Prefer `--splash-zoom: 1` on wide tools so zoom does not push visuals into the header
- Opt-in markers: `data-splash-wide`, `.splash-wide`, `.animation-workspace--wide`, `.global-splash-card--wide`
- Tune: `.{prefix}-fs.tool-intro-fs { --splash-wide-min-height: 300px; --splash-wide-max-height: 380px; }`
- Multi-card rows use `--splash-row-max` (default `720px`)

## Uniform scale-up (no axis distortion)

Root `--splash-zoom` (default `1.1`) enlarges the whole workspace uniformly via `zoom` (transform fallback where needed).

- Opt out or tune per tool: `.xyz-fs.tool-intro-fs { --splash-zoom: 1; }` or `1.2`
- Never use non-uniform `scaleX` / stretched widths to вАЬfillвАЭ dead space

## Internal content rules

- Prefer responsive `clamp()` and fluid graphic sizes in tool CSS.
- Use `flex-shrink: 1`, `min-height: 0`, `min-width: 0` on growing regions when needed.
- Avoid entrance animations with large `translateY` past card edges; prefer opacity/scale.
- Never overlap the headline or Get Started / „Ф„™„Ч„Ь / –Э–∞—З–∞—В—М CTA.

## Multi-card / N-up exceptions

- Side-by-side cards: workspace capped as one unit (`--splash-row-max`); each card keeps native size.
- `.nup-fs` keeps multi-column stage rules (`zoom: 1`).

## Checklist for a new tool splash

1. Gate uses `tool-intro-fs` + `animation-workspace`.
2. Card uses natural aspect (tool CSS); no full-stage `width: 100%` without a max-width вЙ§ 560px.
3. Wide/horizontal designs: `data-splash-wide` (or `width: 90%` + aspect-ratio) and optional `--splash-max-width`.
4. Tune `--splash-zoom` only if the default enlarge is too much/little.
5. Badge inside card; internals donвАЩt spill.
6. i18n CTA keys for en / he / ru.
